    "body": "After running for a few minutes, I see this error only on the TRACE level in the context of the handshake like so:\r\n```\r\n[TRACE] [04-26|13:33:14.877] Accepted connection                      addr=18.139.115.236:45470\r\n[TRACE] [04-26|13:33:15.072] Failed p2p handshake                     id=700e0c7ea0e8a6351d233e6560f315a4a03185d7884335a2d5ebe8efed39d8d4 addr=18.139.115.236:45470 conn=inbound err=\"read tcp 192.168.1.149:30303->18.139.115.236:45470: read: connection reset by peer\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nor so:\r\n```\r\n[TRACE] [04-26|13:24:19.404] Failed RLPx handshake                    addr=78.156.48.121:30303 conn=dyndial err=\"read tcp 192.168.1.149:49847->78.156.48.121:30303: read: connection reset by peer\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think it is ok, because it is just one of the failure reasons there.\r\n\r\nPeers disconnects are also logged with Trace:\r\n```\r\n[TRACE] [04-26|13:29:11.539] Peer disconnected                        id=\"...\" name=Geth/v1.10.18-unstable-f0328f24/linux-amd64/go1.18.1\r\n[TRACE] [04-26|13:29:11.539] ... Error while running peer: reading message: EOF\r\n```\r\n\r\nLet's close for now, and watch If it happens in some other context.\r\n",
